    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "Candidate Summary \u2013 Prompt Engineer (Interview Incomplete)\n\nCandidate:
    Jeude\n\nRole: Prompt Engineer\n\nStatus: Incomplete Interview\n\n\nSummary of
    Responses\n\nIntroduction:\n\nCandidate shared a brief, garbled overview of pursuing
    a BE in computer science, interest in AI projects like a college enrollment app,
    and initial experimentation with ChatGPT prompts, but responses lacked coherence
    and detail.\n\nTechnical Question(s):\n\nNo response provided for the technical
    question on prompting techniques like chain-of-thought or few-shot learning.\n\n\nSection
    Scores\n\nIntroduction: 1.8/10 (5 answers)\n\nResume Questions: 0/10 (0 answers)\n\nTechnical:
    0/10 (0 answers)\n\nBehavioral/Situational: 0/10 (0 answers)\n\nWrap-Up: 0/10
    (0 answers)\n\nOverall Score: 1.8/10 (5)\n\n\nStrengths\n\n- Demonstrated basic
    enthusiasm for AI and prompt engineering.\n\n- Noted personal curiosity from
    experimenting with prompt variations.\n\n\nAreas for Improvement\n\n- Responses
    were incoherent, garbled, and lacked clarity or structure.\n\n- No specific examples,
    projects, or technical details provided.\n\n- Failed to articulate background
    or improvements from prompt tweaks effectively.\n\n\nPreliminary Assessment\n\nThe
    interview is incomplete, covering only introductory questions with no data from
    resume, technical, behavioral, or wrap-up sections. Candidate's low scores reflect
    poor communication and minimal substantive content. This suggests inadequate
    preparation or verbal skills for the role.\n\n\nRecommendations / Next Steps\n\n-
    Reschedule to complete remaining sections, including technical and behavioral
    questions.\n\n- Advise candidate to practice clear, structured responses with
    specific examples.\n\n- Consider screening out if communication issues persist,
    as they are critical for prompt engineering."
